g.text:
I'm being lazy about symbols with MS3 here. It's actually a different switch with only four connections, all of which are normally open.
TPS is also different, only two connections.
Spare TPS pin and spare switch pins are shorted together to show they don't exist and suppress warnings
Note wire 24 is connected to wire 1 here in both left and right position. It's only disconnected in middle position, which isn't shown here
"Wire 12" on pin 4 here isn't really wire 12, it's NC at the other end of the grey cable.
Wire-5 and wire-7 from the direction switch are loose and wrapped in tape down in the back panel.

From left to right relays are 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.
4, 5, 6 are on the second row in this schematic.
